\begin{title}
Characterization, thermal stability, and thermo- mechanical properties of PI(BPDA/PDA) from various precursors
\end{title}

Since it is necessary to ascertain the same degree of imi- dization for PI(BPDA/PDA) from various precursors, the FTIR spectra for PI(BPDA/PDA) from various precursors after the identical imidization process are presented in Fig. 5. The degree of imidization is estimated by the absorbance ratio of 1773 cm–1 band (C2O stretching in imide ring) to the 1517 cm–1 band (C2C stretching in benzene ring in PDA) as shown in Fig. 5. As can be seen in Fig. 5, independent of the differences of precursors, all the PI(BPDA/PDA)’s from various precursors show the same FTIR spectra and an almost identical degree of imi-

